article.headline: Walker scores 17 as Montana State defeats Omaha 76-65
article.description: — Brandon Walker had 17 points in Montana State's 76-65 victory against Omaha on Wednesday night.
article.linkText: Walker scores 17 as Montana State defeats Omaha 76-65
article.story: OMAHA, Neb. -- — Brandon Walker had 17 points in Montana State's 76-65 victory against Omaha on Wednesday night. Walker shot 7 of 11 from the field and 3 for 5 from the line for the Bobcats (4-5). Agbonkpolo added 13 points while shooting 5 for 9, including 3 for 6 from beyond the arc while he also had seven rebounds and four steals. Patrick McMahon had 11 points and shot 3 of 4 from the field and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line. Marquel Sutton led the way for the Mavericks (3-7) with 22 points and seven rebounds. Omaha also got 12 points from Tony Osburn. Isaac Ondekane finished with 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
